-- ANZ Hires Dresdner Kleinwort's Richard Huston as Its Foreign-Exchange Head
-- Candice Zachariahs
-- 2010-07-02T00:25:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/anz-hires-dresdner-kleinwort-s-richard-huston-as-its-foreign-exchange-head.html

          
          
             Australia & New Zealand Banking
Group Ltd. hired  Richard Huston  as global head of foreign
exchange based in Hong Kong.  
 Huston will report to Sydney-based  Steve Bellotti , the
bankâ€™s managing director for global markets, said  Kevin Foley ,
a spokesman for ANZ Bank. Huston, who joined in May, previously
worked at Dresdner Kleinwort Wasserstein as co-head of macro
risk and also spent 11 years at Merrill Lynch, Foley said.  
 ANZ Bank also said it hired  Grant Turley  as a foreign
exchange research assistant based out of Sydney and reporting
to chief economist  Warren Hogan . Grant, who joined last month,
was previously with the Reserve Bank of Australia, Foley said.  
